+# ExecHealth rollout deploy manifest / env contract (v1)
+
+Purpose:
+- fail before starting sensitive rollout-gated jobs if host/container env is incomplete or drifted.
+
+Schema/version:
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_ROLLOUT_PREFLIGHT_SCHEMA_VERSION=exec_health_freeze_rollout_preflight_contract_v1`
+
+Required for guarded jobs:
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_REDIS_AUDIT_URL` -> named user `exec_health_freeze_audit`
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_REDIS_BOOTSTRAP_URL` -> named user `exec_health_freeze_bootstrap`
+- purpose-specific target URL:
+  - ACL policy apply -> `EXEC_HEALTH_REDIS_BOOTSTRAP_URL`
+  - commit-thaw -> `REDIS_URL` with writer user
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_ROLLOUT_PREFLIGHT_CLIENT_NAME`
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_ROLLOUT_PREFLIGHT_LIB_NAME`
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_REDIS_CLIENT_NAME`
+- `EXEC_HEALTH_REDIS_LIB_NAME`
+
+Expected client identities:
+- preflight -> `exec-health-freeze-rollout-preflight-v1` / `exec-health-freeze-audit`
+- acl policy apply -> `exec-health-freeze-acl-policy-v1` / `exec-health-freeze-bootstrap`
+- override commit-thaw -> `exec-health-freeze-override-v1` / `exec-health-freeze-writer`
+
+Checks:
+1. host-side wrapper exports schema version and purpose.
+2. Python preflight validates env contract before Redis connect.
+3. target service validates its runtime env contract on startup.
+4. rollout gate still checked after env validation.
+
+Example manifests:
+- `orderflow_services/deploy/env/exec-health-freeze-acl-policy-apply.env.example`
+- `orderflow_services/deploy/env/exec-health-freeze-override-commit-thaw.env.example`
